The serialization committee is on the 25th... you mean, Christmas?
Yeah, for some reason, it often ends up on Christmas.
The rival inventor's name is Metal Black...
I like that it sounds evil.
It reminds me of the Black Demon Lord.
I thought I would go with color related names for the villains.
and she is in Tanto's class.
So these two will appear at the end of chapter two.
The problem lies with the third chapter.
How will they interact with the protagonist?
But if you do this well, it will definitely be better than the last storyboard you submitted to the serialization committee.
I like how he is going to take over the world little by little.
We both tried to think of petty evil inventions, but it was pretty tough.
We thought of a soda that makes you want to do bad things once you drink it, called Evil Dew...
If you combine that with the chef hat that turns a school lunch into a full course meal...
Let us think harder about it.
Okay then, let us go with Step by step, little by little.
Hey, have some confidence in your work!
Are we really going to be okay for the next serialization meeting?
What do you think of the storyboard that MONEYS wrote?
I know now that my manuscript can become a wonderful manga!
He moved things around quite a bit; is that okay with you?
Of course it isit's far better than my manuscript!
Please have this person do the art.
She has a lot of pride, but she is got an eye for good manga.
I asked you today to write a second chapter, but you have also done a third, and it is all very well done.
But about this God in The children chosen by God...
I think it is best to leave it as an unknown entity of great power, since that would be more like a shounen manga.
That will also pique the readers' interest.
I think it would be better that way.
Are there any other areas that need fixing?
Sorry, let me read it one more time.
If I have Niizuma make a storyboard from this,
it will be more than good enough to pass at the serialization committee.
Can you make a manga that can compete with it...
Today's Friday, so the sample of next week's issue should arrive at our office today.
I heard all her staff are female, but the art is done well, especially the backgrounds.
Oh, I heard Katou's doing that.
And she is the chief assistant, at that.
Katou, I really like this background.
I hope I will be able to draw as well as you soon!
There is a week until the serialization committee.
This time, Tanto will definitely pass!
There are not any promising amateurs this time around, either.
And it is suited for serialization.
We can promote Akina Aiko's manuscript as being written by a Novel Pleiades amateur context winner.
But who is this MONEYS artist?
Is it too risky to serialize an unpublished artist?
No, there is no problem if he can draw this well.
On the contrary, if he can draw this well, I am surprised he has not been published yet.
At any rate, I am submitting this to the committee.
Where did you get such a great amateur?
It is not just the manga authors who are competing.
I am not going to go easy on you.
Frankly, NATURAL is better than Tanto.
Say, why do not you tell Ashirogi Muto that Akina Aiko's manuscript will be submitted to the same committee as theirs?
She is apparently been a rival of Takagi's since middle school.
A storyboard made from Akina Aiko's manuscript will be submitted to the next serialization committee?!
So it is true that she is been your rival since middle school.
She is more like someone I really do not want to lose to.
That is what you call a rival!
Then I am counting on you for the third chapter.
Iwase's already gotten to the serialization committee.
Which means that Hattori's acknowledged her talent, at the very least.
M-Maybe she knows that we are planning on getting married if you get serialized...
There is no way she would tell her that.
If she gets serialized and we do not,
it really will feel like she is getting in our way.
But do not worry, I will not let that happen!
Saiko, let us revise everything, not just the third chapter!
If Miyoshi saw us here together, there would be another misunderstanding.
That last meeting and your letter caused me a lot of trouble.
If we are serialized together after the next committee...
and my manga becomes more popular,
I want you to acknowledge me.
If that happens, I will acknowledge you.
What do you mean by that?
Miyoshi and I are going to register for marriage when I get serialized.
I cannot accept your marriage if I do not!
If you do worse than me, you can do whatever you want.
Well, if you do worse and still get married, you will be pitiful!
I could hold on to my pride that way.
It does not matter if you are better or worsewe're registering when I get serialized.
Your definitely is not a sure bet, though.
I do not really care about a committee I have not submitted anything to.
If you want to leave, then leave!
Hey, let us just sit quietly and wait for now.
Since we are not on the committee, that is all we can do.
I cannot believe that December 25th is our fated day.
If you pass, can we turn in the registration form before the end of the day?
No matter how many times I go through this, the stomachache never goes away!
I see you are in no shape to do that.
The artist is someone Yuujirou had on hand, it seems.
Also, I have never heard of this MONEYS.
At least give us his name and age.
I said the same thing, but Yuujirou refused.
His art and composition is different,
but he forgot to change his habits with layouts.
Is it okay for us to sit in on the meeting?
It is fine, just get in there!
Are both Hattoris on the committee now?
I wonder if they will be offered lead editor positions?
What is the meaning of this?
Niizuma said he wanted to do two manga,
and he has the ability to do so.
It is not possible for an author to have two simultaneous manga!
A one-shot is one thing, but a serialization?!
Each chapter is good on its own,
but it is been a while since I have read something where the second and third chapters step up the pace like this.
Well, I agree that it is good, and I would not want Jack SQ to get it.
There is also the option of having someone other than Niizuma draw it.
I have Akina Aiko's manuscript here.
So you are saying it is only this good because Niizuma's the one who turned it into a storyboard?
I hid the fact that Niizuma drew the art because I feared that you would not accept it if you knew.
Chief Editor, I was objecting to this a little while ago,
but there is no rule that states that an author cannot have two serialized manga at the same time.
There is probably never been an author that could do it before.
Yuujirou, you know how important CROW is to Jack right now, do not you?
If the quality of CROW suffers due to the artist working on two manga simultaneously
Niizuma wants to work on this so badly that if he does not, he will lose motivation.
He is boasting that he will have two excellent manga in Jack and become the number one author!
So if this is serialized, he wants to do it under his real name?
Akina Aiko attends the same college as Aoki Kou, and feels that she is her rival.
She was also Ashirogi Muto's classmate in middle school, and I hear she is been Takagi's rival ever since.
Furthermore, there is a clear rivalry between Niizuma Eiji and Ashirogi Muto
Ugh, I am so nervous about whether or not we will get married, I am going to have a heart attack!
If we register, we should make sure it is after we beat Ayase!
If we get serialized, it will be a nice Christmas present for Azuki.
Hirameki Tanto-kun will begin its serialization in Issue 12!
No way, we are getting married?!
Hey are you listening to me?
with a manuscript by Akina Aiko.
Which means that Niizuma Eiji will have two serialized works in Jack?
What do you mean, he is doing two works at the same time?!
It is not fair to have Niizuma do the art!
There will be one less slot for new authors!
It was agreed that Tanto was much better than last time.
Was this really your scheme, Hattori?
I did it in order for it to pass.
So anything goes as long as it passes?
Anyway, keep working on the first chapter.
I will get you some assistants.
It sounds like the editing department's in an uproar over Eiji doing two manga at once.
Will he be able to manage two manga?
Authors have done three weekly manga in the past.
They must have decided that Eiji could manage it.
And Iwase's getting serialized, even though it is only been half a year since she said she would break into manga.
Hattori and Eiji's help was probably a big factor.
Because Iwase and Eiji are teaming up with Hattori as their editor!
you got your serialization, so why are not you happier?
As of issue 12, Hirameki Tanto-kun will be serialized!
She says we have got talent!
We will get an anime this time, for Saiko and Azuki's sake!
You are coming over tomorrow, right?
Let us practice greeting my parents.
Well, uh, we might have a meeting tomorrow...
Well, you do not have to if you think you will be fine on the fly.
I am counting on you, too, Mashiro.
If someone as good as Niizuma is allowed to have two manga, newbies will not stand a chance!
You cannot say there are not any newbies involved in this.
Whether you are a veteran or a newbie, a good manga is a good manga.
So nothing else matters, as long as it is good?
Then I will ask Oda to draw something!
You would just be a copycat!
If you have something to say, say it to the Chief Editor!
More importantly, has each lead editor informed everyone about the new team?
So I am the new lead, after all!
The new lead editor is Oonishi.
You can be in the serialization committee now.
I guess I will go tell Niizuma.
I will make a report, too, then.
You should be happier about this.
Sorry, but I have never failed to win or pass at anything, whether it be exams or literature.
Then please continue to keep up the good work so that it will not be canceled.
It was just the two of you this time.
And I did not tell you this before, but your artist, MONEYS, is actually Niizuma Eiji, the author of CROW.
It is a popular manga that is been on the front cover many times, and also frequently gets color pages.
We have hidden it up until now, but we are going with Art by Niizuma Eiji for the serialization.
You will not fail with him.
He is the best artist you could possibly have for this.
I would like to meet him at least once.
I do not think you two would mesh well...
Either way, the New Years party is on January 15th.
I am looking forward to it.
Will TakagI mean, Ashirogi be attending this New Years party as well?
I am looking forward to it even more.
Master Niizuma must be happy, too.
Niizuma's got a new serialization, too.
He is drawing the art for a new one.
Is he going to have two manga running in Jack concurrently?
The original work is +NATURAL by Akina Aiko...
Even before the serialization was decided on,
he drew up a rough sketch of the first chapter.
And next time, I will become a lead editor!
What the hell is this I hear about Niizuma doing the art for another serialization?!
Niizuma Eiji, the man with two serializations.
So anything goes if it is good for business?
Do not put it that way.
Fukuda, you stick your nose into other people's business too much.
Two serializations in a weekly magazine?
Compared to that, look at you.
The guy who cannot even finish his year-end work.
I will be done in a few hours.
I am only late because the love-work schedule you made for me got all screwed up!
Sure, she looked better than Aoki in the picture.
But she looked completely different in person!
Next time, I will meet her before I introduce you.
I made it through this year somehow, but I will be counting on you for more motivation next year.
Why do not you just go after her?
If you keep your deadlines, you are free to do as you like with your love life.
It is common for manga authors to get married.
But it is up to Aoki...
That kind of girl is weak against a bit of pressure.
God is on your side, Hiramaru.
But can a manga author make a good living, Akito?
All it takes is one hit, and you will be rolling in dough, Father!
Hey, sorry I cut it short earlier.
Apparently, we are all getting together at Eiji's tomorrow.
What about coming over to my house?
This is part of my job.
We will do it the day after, all right?
Actually, we were classmates in middle school, and we do not get along very well...
If she is pairing up with Niizuma, she should be part of Team Fukuda.
I think she would be happy if we let her into the group.
Iwase... Akina Aiko is interested in Takagi,
but he already has a girlfriend...
Master Niizuma, give her a call.
I do not have her number.
No, I will stay faithful to Aoki.
After the party today, I will take her home in my German car!
Which one of you is Niizuma?
I am looking forward to working together.
Well, it is a gathering where we share opinions on each other's manga, and stuff...
I even looked at Aoki's storyboard for her.
I have confidence in my work!
I would never accept opinions of other authors!
Niizuma, I leave the art to you.
I was kind of expecting things to turn out like this.
She is just like Aoki was two years ago!
Well then, let us have a toast!
And then I will take Aoki home...
Why are you doing two manga?
Is it so that you have something to fall back on if one goes south?
You should devote yourself to CROW.
Yeah, it does seem like an author's attention would be split if he worked on two manga...
And personally, I do not want to lose to Akina Aiko, so you drawing for her is sort of...
I also do not want to lose to +NATURAL.
I am against you drawing the art, since it feels like a ploy by the editorial department.
Do not hurry to your death!
I am not against him working on two serializations,
but I do not want to lose to the second one!
Where did the idea even come from?
Your editor pushed you into this, did not he?
If we do this, It will definitely fire up Ashirogi Muto!
Quit your whining, all of you.
I draw because I want to.
If you have complaints, say them after you make a better manga than mine.
Neither of my manga will lose to any of yours.
It is frustrating, but Niizuma is right.
We will just have to make a manga that is better than his.
Aoki, since it is getting late, please allow me to drive you home.
Aoki, I will take you on my bike, if you do not mind the cold.
God has given up on me.
Takagi, you have got a serialization and a marriage on the way!
But both are a big pain!
We are all connected through our dreams!
